1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with speech manipulation and fluency, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
2. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with audio stream manipulation, which falls under the domain of sound processing. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the impact of speech fluency on listener engagement and comprehension, which falls under the domain of social networks. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a predictive model to learn from professional speech dataset, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - Although less likely, the paper involves computational complexity in terms of processing and manipulating audio streams in real-time.
